# .sanitize-ignore — explicit whitelist for release-sanitize.sh (S3-1)
#
# Format: one path (relative to scanned root) per line; '#' starts comment; blank OK.
# Paths are matched via case glob against the relative file path.
#
# Rule of thumb: only add entries you can defend in a security review.
# Prefer fixing the source over adding a line here.

# ── Intentional test fixtures ────────────────────────────────────────────
# These files carry planted patterns so the scanner's detectors can be tested.
# They are self-documenting test data; the strings are not real credentials.
tests/test_sanitize.sh
tests/test_no_force_bypass.sh
tests/test_credential_patterns.sh
tests/test_sanitize_ignore_hardening.sh
tests/test_sanitize_output_format.sh

# ── Business contact (by design, not a leak) ─────────────────────────────
# SECURITY.md intentionally exposes a real contact email so reporters can
# reach maintainers. Not a secret.
SECURITY.md

# ── Internal dev docs (gitignored, never shipped) ────────────────────────
# These files are listed in .gitignore and excluded by release.sh rsync —
# they never enter a release artifact. Whitelisted here only so that
# `release-sanitize.sh .` (local self-check on repo root) exits clean.
.omc/*
REVIEW.md
GitHub_STANDARD_ANALYSIS.md
HANDOFF.md
HANDOFF.archive.md

# ── superpowers spec/plan docs (internal design records) ─────────────────
# Tracked by git for cross-machine sync (Syncthing) but never enter the
# source tarball or .skill bundle (release.sh rsync excludes docs/super-).
# Contain placeholder emails (security@tkxlab.ai) and Co-Authored-By
# noreply@anthropic.com signatures that are documentation, not real PII.
docs/superpowers/specs/*
docs/superpowers/plans/*

# ── Syncthing conflict quarantine (.gitignored) ──────────────────────────
.syncthing-quarantine-*/*

# ── gitx-sop SOP template (intentional git-identity literal) ─────────────
# noreply@github.com is GitHub's reserved non-routable identity used in the
# generated SOP's `git config user.email` step — documentation, not PII.
# Template is de-hardcoded (placeholders only), TDD-guarded, reviewed.
references/gitx-sop/*
skills/gitx-release/references/gitx-sop/*

# ── Generated release artifacts (not source input) ───────────────────────
# release.sh scans the staged source and the fresh .skill bundle separately.
# Historical Release/* outputs are ignored for whole-repo local self-checks.
Release/*
